# DTW App — Environment Variables
#
# Secrets are now loaded from AWS Secrets Manager at startup.
# .env is no longer used for secrets — do not create a local .env file.
#
# The app authenticates to AWS using:
#   - Local dev: ~/.aws/credentials (run `aws configure` or use AWS SSO)
#   - Production: IAM role attached to the EC2/ECS/Lambda instance
#
# ── Secrets Manager config (override if needed) ────────────────────────────────
# AWS_SECRET_NAME=mwambsganss/dtw   # name of the secret in Secrets Manager
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1              # region where the secret lives
#
# ── Secrets stored in AWS Secrets Manager (mwambsganss/dtw) ───────────────────
# The secret must be a JSON object with these keys:
#
#   FLASK_SECRET_KEY        — random string for Flask session signing
#   S3_BUCKET               — e.g. lilly-dtw-sessions (leave blank to use local filesystem)
#   S3_REGION               — e.g. us-east-1
#   S3_PREFIX               — key prefix inside the bucket (e.g. dtw)
#   LLM_GATEWAY_URL         — https://lilly-code-server.api.gateway.llm.lilly.com
#   LLM_MODEL               — e.g. claude-sonnet-4-6
#   AZURE_CLIENT_ID         — Azure AD app client ID (optional, for frontend MSAL auth)
#   AZURE_TENANT_ID         — Azure AD tenant ID (optional, for frontend MSAL auth)
#   PORT                    — (optional) server port, default 5001
